data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"---\n\n## Cross-Cloud Cost Analysis — Status Report\n\n### Executive Summary\n\n**I cannot deliver the analysis you've requested.** Across **6 audits and 21+ tool calls**, zero bytes of cost data have been retrieved from either AWS or Azure. The MCP proxy remains broken with the same `HTTP 500 — \"Attempt to overwrite 'args' in LogRecord\"` error on every request. I will not fabricate numbers.\n\n---\n\n## What Was Attempted (This Session + Prior)\n\n| # | Tool | Attempt | Status |\n|:-:|------|:-------:|:------:|\n| 1 | `azure_cost_forecast` | New (your request) | ❌ HTTP 500 |\n| 2 | `aws_cost_summary` | Retry #3 | ❌ HTTP 500 |\n| 3 | `aws_cost_by_service` | Retry #3 | ❌ HTTP 500 |\n| 4 | `azure_cost_by_service` | Retry #3 | ❌ HTTP 500 |\n| 5 | `azure_cost_query` (Daily) | Retry #3 | ❌ HTTP 500 |\n| 6 | `call_aws` (CE direct) | Fallback #2 | ❌ HTTP 500 |\n| 7 | `azure_arm_execute` (CostMgmt) | Fallback #2 | ❌ HTTP 500 |\n| | **Cumulative across all audits** | **21 calls** | **0 successful** |\n\n---\n\n## Why I Cannot Answer Your 5 Questions\n\n| Question | Required Data | Available Data |\n|----------|--------------|:--------------:|\n| **1. End-of-month forecast** | `azure_cost_forecast` output + AWS trend data | ❌ None |\n| **2. Unified AWS vs Azure table** | `aws_cost_summary` + `azure_cost_query` | ❌ None |\n| **3. Top 3 optimization opportunities** | Service-level spend from both clouds | ❌ None |\n| **4. Right-sizing / consolidation** | Resource inventory + utilization metrics | ❌ None |\n| **5. Anomalous charges** | Daily cost granularity + historical baseline | ❌ None |\n\n> [!CAUTION]\n> **I will not generate estimated or illustrative cost data.** Any numbers I provide without tool-backed evidence would be fabricated and could lead to incorrect financial decisions. You deserve real data, not guesses.\n\n---\n\n## The Blocking Issue\n\nThe MCP proxy (`openagentic-mcp-proxy` in namespace `openagentic`) has a **Python logging framework bug** that crashes every inbound request before it reaches any cloud API.\n\n```\nError: \"Attempt to overwrite 'args' in LogRecord\"\n```\n\nThis is the **6th consecutive audit** where cloud tools are unavailable:\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart LR\n    A[\"Audits 1–3<br/>ECONNREFUSED<br/>Pod crashed\"] --> B[\"Audit 4<br/>ECONNREFUSED<br/>Total outage\"]\n    B --> C[\"Audit 5<br/>HTTP 500<br/>LogRecord bug\"]\n    C --> D[\"Audit 6 (now)<br/>HTTP 500<br/>Same bug persists\"]\n    style A fill:#dc2626,color:#fff\n    style B fill:#dc2626,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#f59e0b,color:#000\n    style D fill:#f59e0b,color:#000\n```\n\n---\n\n## Immediate Actions to Unblock This Analysis\n\n| Priority | Action | Command |\n|:--------:|--------|---------|\n| **P0** | **Collect the crash traceback** | `kubectl logs -n openagentic -l app=openagentic-mcp-proxy --tail=300` |\n| **P0** | **Rollback to last working image** | `kubectl rollout undo deployment/openagentic-mcp-proxy -n openagentic` |\n| **P0** | **If no prior revision, restart** | `kubectl rollout restart deployment/openagentic-mcp-proxy -n openagentic` |\n| **P0** | **Verify recovery** | `kubectl exec -n openagentic deploy/openagentic-mcp-proxy -- curl -s localhost:8080/health` |\n\n### Likely One-Line Fix\n\nThe bug is almost certainly in a custom log formatter. Look for code like:\n\n```python\n# ❌ BROKEN — triggers \"Attempt to overwrite 'args' in LogRecord\" in Python 3.12+\nrecord.args = sanitized_args\n\n# ✅ FIX — use extra dict or create a new record\nrecord.__dict__['args'] = sanitized_args\n# OR\nlogger.info(message, extra={\"custom_args\": sanitized_args})\n```\n\n---\n\n## What I Will Deliver Once the Proxy is Fixed\n\nOnce even a single tool call succeeds, I will immediately execute the full analysis:\n\n- [ ] **AWS identity** + MTD spend + service breakdown\n- [ ] **Azure subscriptions** + MTD cost query + service breakdown\n- [ ] **Azure end-of-month forecast** (7-day projection)\n- [ ] **Unified cost comparison table** — AWS vs Azure, side-by-side\n- [ ] **Top 3 optimization opportunities** with estimated monthly savings\n- [ ] **Right-sizing recommendations** based on resource utilization\n- [ ] **Anomaly detection** — flag services with unusual spend patterns\n- [ ] **Interactive Sankey diagram** visualizing cost flow across both clouds\n\n---\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> **This is a platform engineering issue, not a permissions issue.** Your credentials are likely fine — the proxy crashes before it ever attempts authentication. The fix is in the MCP proxy codebase, not in IAM policies. Please engage the platform team to apply the rollback or hotfix above, then re-run this query."}

